cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DL 

This paper deals with the study of web complaints, which involves issues related to web governance, copyright enforcement, and online content regulation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also involves issues related to security and privacy, which fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The study of web complaints also involves information retrieval and search engines, which fall under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves the analysis of large-scale data, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
